Homework 16 Solutions

Jonah Fein

Read in data

snails=read.table("snails.csv",header=TRUE,sep = ",")

Part 1a

plot(snails$length,snails$weight,pch=19,xlab="Length",ylab="Weight")

Part 1b

model=lm(weight~length,data=snails)
summary(model)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = weight ~ length, data = snails)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max

## length        6.1670     0.2075   29.71   <2e-16 ***

Part 1c

require(MASS)
## Loading required package: MASS
## 
## Attaching package: 'MASS'
## The following object is masked _by_ '.GlobalEnv':
## 
##     snails
snails$pred=predict(model)
snails$stud_res=stdres(model)
plot(snails$pred,snails$stud_res,pch=19,xlab="Predicted Weight",ylab="Studentized Residual")
abline(a=0,b=0)

qqnorm(snails$stud_res,pch=19)
qqline(snails$stud_res)

Part 1f

snails$log_weight=log(snails$weight)
plot(snails$length,snails$log_weight, xlab="Length",ylab="Ln of Weight",pch=19)

Part 1g

model2=lm(log_weight~length,data=snails)
summary(model2)

Part 1h

snails$predlog=predict(model2)
snails$stud_reslog=stdres(model2)
plot(snails$predlog,snails$stud_reslog,pch=19,xlab="Ln of Weight",ylab="Ln of Studentized Residual")
abline(a=0,b=0)

qqnorm(snails$stud_reslog,pch=19)
qqline(snails$stud_reslog)
